    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n40" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀγανός</span></b>  (cf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">γάνυμαι</span>): <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">pleasant, gentle,
            kindly;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔπεα, δῶρα, βασιλεύς</span> (opp. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χαλεπός</span>), <i><span class="en">Od.
            2.230</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; εὐχωλαι,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 9.499</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 13.357</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> οἷς ἀγανοῖς
            βελέεσσι</span>, ‘with his (her) gentle shafts,’ describing a
          (natural) sudden, painless death dealt by Apollo upon men, by Artemis
          upon women, <i><span class="en">Od. 3.280</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
